<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1679] NodeJS: protocol readString() should treat string as utf8, not binary</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1679</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using Node.js&apos;s Thrift library to talk to Hive:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a) Read back a Hive result that contains utf8 characters&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Get a Javascript string object that contains the correct utf8 sequence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Actual:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Get a Javascript sequence that is indicative of UTF8 double-encoding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Underlying:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In protocol.js, change &quot;readString()&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; var r = this.readBinary().toString(&apos;binary&apos;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;var r = this.readBinary().toString(&apos;utf8&apos;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Per &lt;a href=&quot;http://thrift.apache.org/docs/types/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://thrift.apache.org/docs/types/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;string: A text string encoded using UTF-8 encoding&quot;&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
